The Adviser is powered by one of Australia’s most progressive and successful media businesses. With over of decade of experience, Momentum Media (www.momentummedia.com.au) has been highly awarded for its ability to create energised and connected professional communities.

general.description:
Paul Burgess is a Director of Burgess Paluch and Kaleidoscope Legal Recruitment, managing their recruitment operations across Australia, Asia and New Zealand. Based out of Melbourne, Paul successfully manages recruitment campaigns in the legal sector from private practice Partner level down to the lawyer level, whilst also managing recruitment campaigns for large corporates and government.

Paul is regarded as a leading legal recruiter in Australia with over 18 years recruiting lawyers. Practicing as a lawyer prior to joining the HR & Recruitment industry has given Paul a competitive edge as a legal recruiter. Paul has been a director in three successful businesses and has had a successful career in human resources and management prior to co-founding Burgess Paluch over 15 years ago.

Specialties: Legal Recruitment, executive recruitment, human resources.

general.headline: Director - Legal Recruitment at Ablethorpe Recruitment
general.description:
I am the founder and Director of Legal Recruitment (Australia) at Ablethorpe Recruitment. www.ablethorpe.com

I graduated with a Bachelor of Law and Bachelor of Commerce from Monash University in 1998 and then worked as a solicitor, gaining wide exposure to the law as a Commercial Litigator with a specialty in Trade Practices and Intellectual Property disputes. 

I commenced my career in legal recruitment in 2002, joining Morgan &Banks/TMP Worldwide, which later morphed into Hudson Global Resources.  I have specialised in legal recruitment for the last decade completing assignments within Australia and internationally and have held the positions of Senior Legal Recruiter, Principal Consultant Legal and Manager, Legal.
	
On a functional recruitment level at Ablethorpe Recruitment, I look after legal recruitment at the Partnership and General Counsel level down to junior lawyers across private law firms, corporations and government departments within Australia. I also assist lawyers to obtain roles internationally through affiliates and local internationals.  
	
My clients have included some of Australia’s largest law firms, major international blue chip corporates and also local privately owned corporations as well as public sector bodies and departments.

I remain a member of the Law Institute of Victoria, the Australian Corporate Lawyers Association and also retain my Victorian legal practising certificate.

general.headline: Director at Barnaby Recruitment
general.description:
JOHN COTTON - DIRECTOR RECRUITMENT - ACCOUNTING & AUDIT

John Cotton is a Chartered Accountant and Certified Internal Auditor. He qualified as a Chartered Accountant with Price Waterhouse in Melbourne. Upon leaving the profession, John took the internal audit / risk management route and spent two years as an internal corporate auditor for the film distribution company, United International Pictures, investigating frauds in Chile, Thailand and South Korea, taking over the operations in both Chile and Thailand until General Managers were appointed.

In the mid-90s, he joined KPMG in London to help develop Risk Management methodologies, now recognised in international Risk Management standards and the application of risk to Internal Audit In 2001 John started a consultancy in London helping clients identify risks, mitigating their controls and implement the processes needed to improve operations. This role expanded upon the introduction of the SEC listing requirements of the Sarbanes Oxley Act in the USA. He project managed the Sarbanes Oxley implementation for the NASDAQ listed wireless telco Airspan Networks Inc., and was heavily involved in SOx projects for National Australia Bank and the Allied Irish Bank.

After 18 years international experience, having worked in over 30 countries, John returned to Australia in 2006 and took on an 18 month contract with Deloitte to run the outsourced internal audits for Orica and Sigma Pharmaceuticals.

John specialises in recruiting for the Accounting Profession, Accountants in Industry as well as Internal Audit and Technical Accounting roles.

Call John on 0448-877-789 for a confidential discussion or email him at john@barnabyrecruitment.com.au
